parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own without any warning
causing the vehicle to move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drivetrain malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially on highways.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts to Neutral or loses power
causing the vehicle to come to a stop; the vehicle may display error messages related to drivetrain malfunction

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of safety systems can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to lose critical safety features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the front control arm can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: and may require extensive repairs to the axle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: and erratic behavior of the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electronic stability control system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Uncontrollable movement of the steering wheel
and erratic behavior of the backup assistance system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning of the Adaptive Cruise Control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or brake unexpectedly, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially putting occupants and other road users at risk.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or brakes suddenly
fails to stop or accelerate reliably
and displays reduced driver assistance support messages.
